		<section> <!-- Fast Facts Page 1 -->
          <h2>Did You Know</h2>
          <ul>
			<li>A black hole is a region of spacetime from which nothing can escape, even light!</li>
            <li>Black holes have the most matter stuffed into the least space of any objects in the universe!</li>
            <li>The boundary of the region from which no escape is possible is called the event horizon.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

		 <section><!--how to make a black hole-->
			<h2>How to Become a Black Hole</h2>
            <img style="float:left;margin-right:50px;width:50%;height:50%;" data-src="/img/black-holes/supernova.jpg" />
			<p>A star burns energy in the form of nuclear fuel. When a star runs out of fuel, it can no longer generate any push against the gravity of all its mass. The gravity forces everything toward the center of the star and the core collapses into a black hole.</p>
          </section>

