        <section> <!-- Stellar Black Holes -->
			<h2>Stellar Black Holes</h2>
            <img style="float:left;margin-right:50px;width:50%;height:50%;" data-src="/img/black-holes/stellar-black-hole.jpg" />
            <p>Stellar black holes are made when the center of a very big star falls in upon itself, or collapses. The outer layers of the star explode in what is called a <i>supernova</i>.</p>
          </section>

          <section> <!--Supermassive Black Holes-->
			<h2>Supermassive Black Holes</h2>
            <img style="float:left;margin-right:50px;" data-src="/img/black-holes/supermassive-black-hole.jpg" />
            <p>These super-sized black holes are formed as the result of many black holes combining into one enormous black hole. Scientists think they were made at the same time as the galaxy they are in.</p>
            <p></p>
          </section>

