			<h2>If black holes are black & in space, how can we see them?!</h2><br/>
			<p>Scientists can see how the strong gravity of a black hole affects the stars and gas around it. Scientists can study stars to find out if they are flying around, or orbiting, a black hole.</p><br/>
			<p>When a black hole and a star are close together, high-energy light is made. This kind of light can not be seen with human eyes. Scientists use satellites and telescopes in space to see the high-energy light.</p>
